    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked kale & spinach </strong>to a<strong> food processor </strong>with your <strong>basil</strong>, <strong>flaked almonds</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your<strong> white wine vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> pesto</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
